Try www.gamasutra.com, and look through the archives, they had an article
about lightmaps. A very good article can be found on
http://members.home.com/milod, under game tech (in Color and lighting).


Basically, it's a second texture that is applied to the
same triangle in a special way, namely the texture values are multiplied.
A special blending mode is normally needed, which isn't available on any
Amiga board, but the "normal" alpha blending (source, 1-source) can also
be used with monochrome lightmaps. The topic is very complex, but the
Gamasutra article explains it rather well..

